Q1Ô∏è‚É£ Basic Encapsulation Create a class Student: private variables: id, name public getters & setters set values and print them

Goal: Hide data using private and access via getters/setters 

// Step 1: Create Student class
class Student {

    // Step 2: Declare private variables (data hiding)
    private int id;
    private String name;

    // Step 3: Setter methods (set values)
    public void setId(int id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public void setName(String name) {
        this.name = name;
    }

    // Step 4: Getter methods (get values)
    public int getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }
}

// Step 5: Test in main class
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Student s = new Student();
        s.setId(10);
        s.setName("Ayush");

üß† Interview line:

Data is private and accessed using public getters and setters.

        System.out.println(s.getId() + " " + s.getName());
    }
}
